{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Strengthen laws on Phone Theft & stolen data",
        "additional_details": "According to the recent crime statistics, phone theft has surged, particularly in urban areas.\r\nMany thefts can involve violence or intimidation, making it a serious safety concern.\r\nPhones are stolen and quickly resold or stripped for parts, creating a lucrative criminal industry.\r\nPersonal and sensitive data (bank details, photos, private communications) can often be compromised.\r\nVictims can suffer emotional distress, privacy violations, and financial risks (such as fraud or identity theft).",
        "background": "Introduce harsher punishments for phone theft, regardless of the perpetrator\u2019s age. Recognize the loss of software, data, and personal information as a significant factor in legal proceedings.\r\nClassify the theft and misuse of personal data from stolen devices as a specific offence.",
